comments.body:
I believe Import statement is not suitable in Emscripten's context because this typing declaration file is usually not meant to be exported as a module.

Emscripten itself not a module nor a library actually. It is a C/C++ => WebAssembly compiler toolchain. It generates WebAssembly (.wasm) + a customizable wrapper JS code  (this is usually not a module, it's often more like a standalone JS application.) + optional HTML file as output.

@type/emscripten is to give typing definitions inside of the wrapper JS code, not outside.
